HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 172
BY REPRESENTATIVES WALTERS, JACKSON, AND PHELPS
COMMENDATIONS: Commends AmeriCorps Seniors Southern University at Shreveport
Caddo/Bossier Foster Grandparent Volunteer Program on forty-six years of service
to children and designates May 1, 2026, as AmeriCorps Seniors Foster Grandparent
Volunteer Day in Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend AmeriCorps Seniors Southern University at Shreveport Caddo/Bossier Foster
3 Grandparent Volunteer Program for forty-six years of exceptional service and to
4 designate Friday, May 1, 2026, as AmeriCorps Seniors Foster Grandparent
5 Volunteer Day in Louisiana.
6 WHEREAS, service in AmeriCorps promotes bridge-building, collaboration, and
7 leadership skills, and AmeriCorps programs bring together people from different
8 backgrounds, generations, and geographic locations; and
9 WHEREAS, for more than five decades, millions of AmeriCorps Seniors volunteers
10 in the Foster Grandparent Program have played an important role in strengthening
11 communities by sharing their experience, knowledge, and accomplishments with the
12 individuals they serve; and
13 WHEREAS, this nationwide program offers seniors, who are fifty-five years of age
14 or older, the opportunity to serve as one-on-one mentors, tutors, and caregivers to
15 economically disadvantaged youth; the program serves to improve behavioral and
16 educational outcomes for students with special and exceptional needs, helps children who
17 suffer from abuse or neglect, and provides support to children of veterans or who have
18 deployed family members; it also serves more than two hundred eighty thousand special
19 needs children through a network of various organizations and helps guide students to higher
20 academic achievement; and
